def: One who practices or advocates polygyny. H. Spenser.
To abash; to disconcert or be disconcerted or put out ofcountenance. [Obs.]His countenance was bold and bashed not. Spenser.
Of or pertaining to a larva.
That stage in the development of the ovum in which the outercells of the morula become more defined and form the blastoderm.
A weight of the metric system, being one million grams; ametric ton.
, a. Doing or producing good; performing acts of kindness andcharity; characterized by beneficence.The beneficent fruits of Christianity. Prescott.
One who assays. Specifically: One who examines metallic ores orcompounds, for the purpose of determining the amount of anyparticular metal in the same, especially of gold or silver.
A contrivance for exhibiting and measuring the refraction oflight.
Growing or developing within cartilage; -- applied esp. todeveloping bone.
A collection of hymns; a hymn book.
